Skeleton.
Ectosomal skeleton is difficult to discern since there are many blackish granular cells (
Fig. 59A
). The choanosomal skeleton consists of an irregular isotropic reticulation with 1–3 spicules at all sides (
Fig. 59B
). Single spicules protrude outside the surface (
Fig. 59A
).

Distribution. Mexico (current record), other countries in the Caribbean Sea (
Alvarez et al. 2002
).
